  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to access the \"Password\" input box so that I would be able to recover my account. \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: It's not possible to enter any password in the \"\"Password\" field when using iPad Mini A1432\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nTo be able to enter my password.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nIt's not possible so I'm stuck and can't recover my account. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Open Status on iPad Mini A1432 or similar device. \r\n2. Navigate to the \"Add existing account\" menu. \r\n3. Try to enter your password in the dedicated \"Password\" input box. \r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nImplementing at least one of the following options should be fine:\r\n\r\n- To be able to scroll down to the \"Password\" input box\r\n- To be able to select it no matter that it's not completely visible\r\n- To be able to hide the virtual keyboard.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: 0.9.19 (6031)\r\n* Operating System: iOS\r\n\r\n![1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5781465/41457337-01657a6a-708c-11e8-9bd4-759e08f0e034.jpg)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
